Gun Tests Staff | July 29, 2015
Gun maker Forjas Taurus SA has agreed to settle a $30 million class-action suit with plaintiffs who claim that some Taurus handgun safeties, even when engaged, may allow the gun to fire if it is dropped, according to a review of court documents. More 

California Dusts Off 1923 Law To Ban Advertising of the Sale of Handguns by Dealers »
Gun Tests Staff | July 20, 2015
California has argued that a provision of California Penal Code section 26820 enacted in 1923 prevents the displaying of any “handgun or imitation handgun, or placard advertising the sale or transfer thereof” anywhere in or on their store that can be seen outside their store by passersby. More 

